begin_memory_text: I think we spoke about our relationships and how long we've been with our significant others. She told me I need to get married to my girlfriend of 7.5 years.
middle_memory_text: We spoke about what we do for income and eventually made it to the topic of politics where we learned we were both supporters of President Donald J. Trump.
end_memory_text: We talked about what I wanted to accomplish in life and we also spoke about how my dad decided he was gay after being married to my mom for 25 years.
rest_of_day_open: Hopefully it gets better. I haven't had any coffee this morning since I had a doctors appointment and didn't want to get bubble guts in the middle of it. As a result, I now have a massive headache. Hopefully I'll be able to go for a few more runs this week and work some on the delivery apps.
critical_positive: What worked well is that we were both polite and respectful to each other and had plenty to talk about for the whole conversation. We were both the same politically, so it gave us some interesting things to talk about. She gave me some insight on marriage that I think will help me in the future.
critical_negative: I would say that our age difference made it slightly harder to relate to one another, as well as our occupation level differences. She was further in life than myself, married, and with children. I found it a little difficult to relate as I am unmarried without a formal education.

begin_memory_text: We talked about where he lived and grew up; that he traveled around since his dad was in the military. We talked about where he lives now and his girlfriend. We talked about what sort of work he does. I shared a bit about the same things (where I live, what I do, my family).
middle_memory_text: We discussed how we got involved with this survey and on Prolific. We talked about political affiliation and what we believe about how they place people together for these conversations. We discussed political rallies and Trump.
end_memory_text: At the end of the conversation, we talked about some of his family issues. He shared some hard things about his dad and mom, who are divorced, and how the negative events impacted him and his brothers.
rest_of_day_open: I know that I will spend a lot of time cooking and cleaning. I hope to play quite a bit with my two sons. I am looking forward to serving my husband dinner each night. I know that I will be very tired, but very content at the end of each day.
critical_positive: I was able to ask many questions and Logan gave honest responses that he was willing to elaborate on. He also asked me some questions and gave me a chance to participate in a reciprocal communication. He was friendly and smiled, as well as looked at the screen. I appreciate that he was willing to share some more vulnerable information about his life.
critical_negative: The conversation really did go well overall, and there was little that didn’t go well. If anything, I think that there were things he shared with me that I would have liked to be able to question more about or speak more to, but would not have been appropriate on a first conversation. I also don’t think it would have been appropriate for me as a women to go to much deeper with a man who is not my husband, without my husband present.
